# RUN: tianchenrv-rvv-q4-0-q8-0-shape-selection-test | FileCheck %s

# The N3 capability/resource-aware autotuner for the ggml Q4_0 x Q8_0 and the
# Family-A sibling Q8_0 x Q8_0 block-dots: the COMPILER SELECTS the kernel shape,
# DERIVED from capability + resource facts. The cost model is capability-BLIND;
# capability enters ONLY through the legality prune, so the SAME argmin diverges
# by capability -- a Zvl128b (full-V) target selects the strip-elided shape, a
# non-Zvl128b target has the elided shapes pruned and the same argmin selects the
# robust shape. Flipping ONLY the Zvl128b fact flips the shape (derived, not a
# constant). The vreg-budget prune binds when shrunk; the Zvl128b derivation is
# real ISA reasoning. The q8_0 sibling shares the cost FORMULA + selector but is
# fed its own per-anchor reduction count (m2 dominates -- the structural diff).

# CHECK: N3 Q4_0 cost model is capability-blind + measurement-calibrated (robust U-curve min@2, elided min@4, mf4 loses)
# CHECK: N3 Zvl128b target selects (m1, factor=4, elided) -- the ggml beat
# CHECK: N3 non-Zvl128b target prunes all elided shapes and selects (m1, factor=2, robust) -- the robust optimum
# CHECK: N3 flipping ONLY the Zvl128b fact flips strip_elision elided<->robust (derived, not a constant)
# CHECK: N3 vreg-budget prune binds: a 3-vreg budget prunes all (fail-closed); a 5-vreg budget prunes the wider m1 footprint
# CHECK: N3 Zvl128b derivation: rv64gcv=>true, zve32x/zve64x=>false, explicit zvl128b+/=>true (real ISA reasoning)
# CHECK: N3 q8_0 cost model is capability-blind + structurally ordered (m2 dominates m1 dominates mf4; shallow depth => robust AND elided min@2)
# CHECK: N3 q8_0 Zvl128b target selects (m2, factor=2, elided) -- the measured optimum (shallow depth saturates the unroll at 2)
# CHECK: N3 q8_0 non-Zvl128b target prunes all elided shapes and selects (m2, factor=2, robust) -- the robust optimum
# CHECK: N3 q8_0 flipping ONLY the Zvl128b fact flips strip_elision elided<->robust (derived, not a constant)
# CHECK: N3 q8_0 vreg-budget prune binds: a 3-vreg budget prunes all (fail-closed); an 8-vreg budget prunes the wider m2 footprint
# CHECK: N3 the cost-minimizing factor EMERGES from the DERIVED latency depth (shallow=>2, deep=>4); insensitive to the exact deep length (derived, not a per-kernel lookup)
# CHECK: N3 latency depth is a DERIVED sum (base product->reduce 2 + format decode prefix): q8_0=2, q4_1=4, q4_0=7
# CHECK: N3 q4_0 costs are BYTE-identical to the pre-refactor model (deep depth 7 => overflow term inert; additive)
# The Family-B sibling (q4_1 x q8_1, scale+MIN): the SAME machinery selects a
# structurally NEW kernel's shape; q4_1's depth (4) is DERIVED from its shorter
# unsigned-nibble decode, and the picks match q4_0's (depth >= max factor).
# CHECK: N1+N3 q4_1 (Family-B) Zvl128b selects (m1, factor=4, elided) via the SAME cost model + its derived depth 4
# CHECK: N1 q4_1 (Family-B) non-Zvl128b prunes elided, selects (m1, factor=2, robust) -- divergence by ONE capability fact
# CHECK: N3 q4_1 costs match the depth-blind formula (depth 4 >= max factor => overflow inert); the depth is derived, the picks match q4_0's
# CHECK: RVV N3 Q4_0 + Q8_0 + Q4_1 capability/resource-aware shape selection tests passed
